## ğŸ“Š Evaluation Metrics

Although the model is unsupervised, available labels were used **only for evaluation**:

* Confusion Matrix
* Precision / Recall / F1-score
* ROC-AUC using anomaly scores

This provides a realistic view of how well anomalies align with actual fraud cases.

---

## ğŸ“ˆ Visual Insights

* Fraud vs non-fraud distribution
* Transaction amount patterns
* Balance behavior before vs after transactions
* PCA-based visualization of anomalies

These visuals help interpret model behavior and validate results.

---

## ğŸš€ Key Outcomes

* Successfully identified anomalous transactions
* Clear separation between normal and suspicious behavior
* Scalable pipeline suitable for real-world deployment

